task.summary: Default task
Added new implementation of finding median of two sorted arrays with varying lengths. Should be able to handle length of odd & even.
Cleaned routine names for bubble, insertion, and selection.
Fixed compilation error; this weas due to moved method signator via refactoring.
Fixed implementations to sort algorithms and added better unit tests.
Added new implementation to tower of hanoi.
Fixed implementation of sum of consecutive integers for recursion and also provided iterative method.
Added better support as template for the bubble sort; There is now a harness for the basic sorts.
Fixed implementation bug with insertion; offset of 0. start element needed to be set at 1 so that we can insert to the left of the partition.
Added factorial class and also refactoring of basic math algorithms
Added factorial class and also refactoring of basic math algorithms
Added new algorithm implemenations based on ideas for arrays & lists.
Moved sumOfDigitsTarget to math package.
fixed bubble sort implementation to allow for 0 offset or 1 offset. You can start the compartion for [j] & [j+1] or ( [j-1] && [j]
Added new implementation of sorts algorithm for merge; and improvement to selection by using for loop instead of while loop.
Fixed selection and other implementations to use abstract utility class. This is to enforce all signature to look the same without regards to underlying implementations.
Implemented new and improvied version of quicksort & mergsort using the low & high index strategy. This is conceptually clear and is reflected by most algorithm implementation.
Javadoc'ed the quick & merge sort.
Changed implementation of union & intersection to return lists.
Cleaned up implemenation of stack using array as the ADT.
Cleaned up find mediam of two sorted array routine.
Moved single linked list implemenation to *.list package
Ditto for Doubly Linked Lisat
Added implementation of permuation of substring.
Added height and max width of a binary tree.
fixed unit tests. Still need to address Integer[] vs int[]; the conversion is being done on a shadow array which is not what we want.
Added unit teests for the sort algorithms. It's a little bit more comprehensive this time.
Added Node definition for list classes.
Test unit clean up.
Added test unit for merge sort
Added implementation of serializer and deserializer for binary tree.
Added two more codec implementing the serializer & deserializer for the binary tree.
New implemenation using LinkedList for serializing and deserializing the BST.
Moved the BST implemenation to *.tree* package.
added a missing file for the preorder implementation of bst.
Added string enecoder for serializing duplicate characters found in a given string. For example, 'aaabbfggd' should yield 'a3b2f1g2d1';
Migrated Queue implemention to array package since we are demonstrating use of Array as the implementation of a simple queue.
fixed implementation in sorts.
Simple cleanup
Added new support for math specific algorithms; particularly around bits manipulations.
Major refactoring of code to place logical placements of algorithms and data structures.
New text search implemenation based on naive, rabin-karp, knuthmorrisprate, and boyer-moore methods.
Imroved the search of min values in an array.
fixed some bit manipulation routines. Added examples of calculating the hammer weight of the decimal number.
